        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 28 at 2:46PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 243 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a few high based showers
and thunderstorms capable of producing strong wind gusts of 50 to 55
mph along a line extending from 7 miles north of Crane to 10 miles
west of Grandfalls to 11 miles west of Marfa Municipal Airport.
Movement was northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Crane, Marfa, Fort Davis, Balmorhea, Grandfalls, Valentine, McDonald
Observatory, Saragosa, Bloys Camp, Davis Mountains State Park, Camp
Mitre Peak, Balmorhea Lake, Marfa Municipal Airport, Balmorhea State
Park, Toyah Lake, Imperial Reservoir, Star Mountain, Royalty,
Toyahvale, and Buffalo Trail Scout Camp.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 10 between mile markers 195 and 235.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
